## 📱 ALTERNATIVE: cURL Commands

If Thunder Client is giving you trouble, use these terminal commands:

### Signup:
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5005/auth/signup \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"curl@example.com","username":"curluser","password":"Curl123!"}'
```

### Login:
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5005/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"curl@example.com","password":"Curl123!"}'
```

### Verify (replace TOKEN with your actual token):
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:5005/auth/verify \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN"
```

